      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for your search:\n\n## \"Discovering Latent Knowledge in Language Models Without Supervision\"\n\n**Authors:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Collin Burns, Haotian Ye, Dan Klein, Jacob Steinhardt"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Venue:** "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "International Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR), 2023"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Links:**\n- **arXiv:** https://arxiv.org/abs/2212.03827\n- **OpenReview:** https://openreview.net/forum?id=ETKGuby0hcs\n- **ICLR Virtual Poster:** https://iclr.cc/virtual/2023/poster/11480\n- **GitHub:** https://github.com/collin-burns/discovering_latent_knowledge\n\n### Summary\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Existing techniques for training language models can be misaligned with the truth: if we train models with imitation learning, they may reproduce errors that humans make; if we train them to generate text that humans rate highly, they may output errors that human evaluators can't detect."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors propose circumventing this issue by directly finding latent knowledge inside the internal activations of a language model in a purely unsupervised way."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Specifically, they introduce a method for accurately answering yes-no questions given only unlabeled model activations. It works by finding a direction in activation space that satisfies logical consistency properties, such as that a statement and its negation have opposite truth values."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " This method is called **Contrast-Consistent Search (CCS)**.\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Despite using no supervision and no model outputs, their method can recover diverse knowledge represented in large language models: across 6 models and 10 question-answering datasets, it outperforms zero-shot accuracy by 4% on average."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Additional Context\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Collin Burns is a second-year ML PhD at Berkeley, working with Jacob Steinhardt and Dan Klein. His focus is on making language models honest, interpretable, and aligned."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors now recommend using https://github.com/EleutherAI/elk, which is an improved code base."
      }
    ],
